min traces the interplay between anticolonial thought and practice across key thinkers, interweaving history and textual analysis. He shows how these insights broaden the political and intellectual horizons open to us today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDecolonizationzCanada. 0aDecolonizationzUnited States. 0aIndians of North AmericazCanadaxGovernment relations. 0aIndians of North AmericazUnited StatesxGovernment relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  asovereignty, decolonization, self-determination, citizenship, Indigenous, earthmaking, resurgence, ecology, internationalism, remapping.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079732940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226827278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226827278/original  a978-3-11-079732-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles